  "label": "Chalksalt Bastion",
  "description": "Chalksalt Bastion is a minor asteroid in the Saltharrow System, maintaining a stable, charted orbit within the system’s particulate belts and established transit lanes. Its surface consists of pale, salt-bright regolith fractured by long tensile seams, a geological record of Saltharrow’s pronounced gravitic gradients. The body’s low gravity preserves steep talus slopes and sharp-edged scarps, giving the asteroid a distinctly faceted silhouette against the primary star’s hard white radiance.",
